      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS BLUE STORK (8) was a beaten favourite in a higher-graded race last start but still continued her strong form in finishing third at Newcastle. That gave her five wins and two placings from her last seven starts. Draws on the back row but came from a similar barrier to win here three back and she is suited dropping in class. AMERICAN BOXER (3) produced a good effort at his latest appearance, finishing second over 1609m at Menangle. Came from the back row to place here last month and should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. HESHARLEY (9) has to come into calculations on the back of some consistent form, putting together a string of top-four finishes since coming from this row to win at this circuit and distance. DELIGHTFULLY SWEET (10) is first up for five months but has won when fresh before and was readied with two city trials, placing in the latest.",
